  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book \"Cold War Triangle,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2021, has maintained a commercial presence with listings on platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads. Despite the lack of citations or online discourse, the book's connection to themes of sustainability and policy relevance indicates its potential impact in ongoing academic conversations.</p>\n\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Cold War Triangle,\" published in 2021 by Leuven University Press, reflects a significant scholarly contribution within the context of post-war studies. The absence of formal citations or mentions on social media platforms suggests a limited engagement at this point; however, the book\u2019s commercial linkage through platforms like Amazon and Goodreads indicates an ongoing interest that may develop over time.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">The work\u2019s relevance is somewhat bolstered by its inferred connection to sustainability and policy concerns, rated at a strength of 0.55. This suggests that while the book may not yet have garnered extensive public conversation, it touches upon issues that resonate within current academic and practical frameworks, specifically in relation to the Sustainable Development Goals.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">Furthermore, while the book is not currently represented in knowledge repositories or community discourse platforms, its existing presence in commercial circles plays a vital role in increasing visibility. Over time, as discussions on cold war themes evolve, the book may find its niche in academic syllabi or public discourse.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">Moving forward, the potential for engagement with scholarly networks remains significant. As research on related themes progresses, \"Cold War Triangle\" could yield insights that align with contemporary studies, fostering a renewed examination of its content and consequently enhancing its impact and visibility in scholarly communications.</p>",
